    "body": "Solidity storage variables are mapped to hash keys according to http://solidity.readthedocs.io/en/develop/miscellaneous.html#layout-of-state-variables-in-storage. The keys are stored in a Merkle Patricia trie for the specific account (and the main state trie contains all the accounts). To access them you'll need to use https://godoc.org/github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/core#BlockChain and access the state associated with a block, which will give you the methods to iterate over an account's storage entries.\r\n\r\nNote however, that there's no direct information available that can tell you which hash corresponds to which contract field. That depends on a lot of stuff and the Solidity compiler.",
